BITTERSWEET NEWS!

We are moving out of our Main Venue that services weddings and large events, consolidating, and will be working solely out of our STUDIOS (173 E. Main St. Suite #2) starting February 2023 and beyond. 

We are sad this chapter is closing with our first building that started it ALL, but we are excited that it will possibly make way for a family restaurant that will serve our community as well. 

We will continue to work with our amazing renters in our studios for small events, parties, classes, co-working spaces and more! We have lots in store for those spaces so stay tuned there. 

We will continue to expand our services to include more event decor & management (both at our studios and with options available for other locations) and offer more photography services, styled shoots, styled sets, content shoots for professionals, professional classes, business consulting and more.

In the meantime, stop into the main Venue (142 E. main) for our MOVING SALE January 27-28th. 10am-6pm

We will be selling extra furniture, props, decor and anything we don’t have room for at our other space. 

Thank you for being on this adventure with us and supporting us as we shift and pivot. All of our love! 

THE VENUE TEAM

•ANNOUNCEMENT!• 
Seasons of life change, we pivot in our focus and some things come FULL CIRCLE! I’m so excited to be opening up my schedule for PHOTO SHOOTS again! 

It’s been 6 years since I’ve “officially” marketed for shoots & I’ll admit I’m so very excited to make them a more regular part of my schedule again. I’ve missed the constant creativity! 

I never quit, but had to cut back when other things kept me busy so I haven’t marketed openings in awhile. From now on my openings will be consistent but still somewhat limited, so they will likely go fast! 
 
I’ll be posting the link to schedule shoots along with my updated pricing on my website & social-soon! (#staytuned)

But for now if you have an interest in:
• dance shoots
• high school seniors 
• engagement/ bridal
• baptism/mission shoots
• headshots
• business branding or content shoots…

Reach out via text for availability and pricing!

I’ve known that Jesus was my Savior since my youth. Experiences through childhood and my teen years solidified that feeling in my heart. But it wasn’t until my Sophomore-Junior years of High School that I really came to understand what that meant and how it applied to me.  Before then I misunderstood the Atonement and didn’t understand how to apply in my life.

The shifts that came with insight from the spirit later in High School & on into the early years of my marriage, changed EVERYTHING for me! I have never been the same. 

I am so grateful for what the Savior has done.
He did what NO OTHER could. 

His suffering brought new mercies, forgiveness for mistakes & sin, peace in trials, ALL forms of healing, life eternal, and the possibility for true joy in this messy journey of life. 

All my loves in this life are mine because of HIM! 

Death has no sting because of Him. 

I can do hard things because of Him. 

I will see Him again one day because of what He suffered for me in Gethsemane.

I am redeemed because of the agony He bore under the sting and tear of rod and lash. 

Because of the ridicule & persecution He endured while mocked and crowned with piercing thorns.

Because of the burdens He shouldered as He carried his own cross, step after horrific step, up to the hill where He would die for all the children of God. 

Because of His love, forgiveness, and endurance in His final agony on the cross. 

Because He promised to lay down His life for us, and ultimately kept His promise! (He delivered his spirit at His own word, no man had the power to take it from Him.)

Because of all this, and everything I cannot fathom, understand or even try to describe… I KNOW that He is the Son of God, our Lord & deliverer. Our ALL!

Rigby, ID friends! Ready to make some extra cash off items you no longer wear/use/need? Join the #thriftingmademodern trend by purging your home & closets and consigning name brand, on trend and great condition pieces at @indigomarket.rigby! 

Indigo Market is a curated, market style store for buyers & sellers offering new, pre-loved, gently used, name brand/vintage, handmade and artisan goods, gifts and apparel. 

We officially open Friday 1/19/24 and are ready to help you “out-with-the-old” to make space in your life for new & exciting things when you consign with us. 

Just fill out our online consignment form at www.indigo-market.com/consign, learn more about consignment details on that page & then drop off your items in store Monday-Friday 10-5pm (starting 1/19/24, or the week before by appointment.) 

We can’t wait to work with you & offer our community a unique shopping & selling experience! 

📍 Details on available vendor space & selling at Indigo as a business vendor, COMING SOON!

Say hello to my fun, new business endeavor! @indigomarket.rigby. This is been an amazing (and tiring) project to take on with my mom, daughters and best friend Chantri at @thread.ology.

Who is ready to come shop? 6 days and counting!
